Can use ROOT to compile file instead of using a Makefile!


root -l -b -q 'FluxCalculatorLoop.cxx++'

	•	-l → no splash screen.
	•	-b → batch mode (no graphics).
	•	-q → quit when done.
	•	cxx++ → compile and build a shared library.

and then in the python file add:
import ROOT
ROOT.gSystem.Load("FluxCalculatorLoop_cxx.so")
fcl = ROOT.FluxCalculatorLoop()
